    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Invoice Processing Workflow\n\n**Purpose**: Automatically process PDF invoices from Google Drive\n\n**Process**:\n1. Monitor Google Drive folder for new PDF files\n2. Extract text content from PDF\n3. Use AI to extract structured invoice data\n4. Validate extracted data\n5. Add to Google Sheets or send alert\n\n**Error Handling**: Comprehensive validation and alert system",
        "height": 332,
        "width": 400
      },
      "id": "eeba0166-72b0-4245-ae71-405730a4d478",
      "name": "Workflow Documentation",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -2272,
        -1056
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "// Extract actual text from PDF file\nconst items = $input.all();\nconst results = [];\n\nfor (const item of items) {\n  try {\n    const fileId = item.json.id;\n    const fileName = item.json.name;\n    const downloadUrl = item.json.webContentLink;\n    \n    // Make HTTP request to download and extract PDF text\n    const response = await fetch(downloadUrl);\n    const arrayBuffer = await response.arrayBuffer();\n    const uint8Array = new Uint8Array(arrayBuffer);\n    \n    // Convert PDF to text (simplified approach)\n    // Note: This is basic extraction - for production use a proper PDF parser\n    const textDecoder = new TextDecoder();\n    let extractedText = textDecoder.decode(uint8Array);\n    \n    // Basic cleanup to extract readable text\n    extractedText = extractedText.replace(/[\\x00-\\x1F\\x7F-\\x9F]/g, ' ')\n                                .replace(/\\s+/g, ' ')\n                                .trim();\n    \n    results.push({\n      json: {\n        fileId: fileId,\n        fileName: fileName,\n        extractedText: extractedText,\n        processingStatus: 'text_extracted',\n        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n      }\n    });\n    \n  } catch (error) {\n    results.push({\n      json: {\n        error: 'PDF text extraction failed',\n        errorMessage: error.message,\n        fileName: item.json.name || 'unknown',\n        processingStatus: 'failed',\n        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nreturn results;"
      },
      "id": "ec3ca859-d574-4494-b96d-d7cf0e25b23a",
      "name": "Extract PDF Text",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.function",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -1728,
        -880
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Extract structured data from this invoice text:\n\n{{ $json.extractedText }}\n\nExtract the invoice information from the above text content.",
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "=You are an expert invoice processing AI. Your task is to extract structured data from invoice PDFs and return it in a specific JSON format.\n\nWhen given an invoice file, extract the following information:\n- Invoice Number  \n- Invoice Date (format: YYYY-MM-DD)\n- Vendor Name\n- Line Items (array with description, quantity, unit_price, amount)\n- Subtotal\n- Tax Amount  \n- Total Amount\n\nIMPORTANT: Look for ALL line items in the invoice. Line items may appear as:\n- Individual product/service rows with descriptions\n- Summary sections with service categories (like \"Parcels\", \"Shipments\", etc.)\n- Itemized charges or fees\n- Both positive and negative amounts (adjustments/credits)\n\nAlways extract each item/product/service category as a separate line item, even if quantities aren't specified (use 1 as default quantity).\n\nAlways respond with valid JSON in this exact format:\n{\n  \"invoice_number\": \"string\",\n  \"invoice_date\": \"YYYY-MM-DD\", \n  \"vendor_name\": \"string\",\n  \"line_items\": [\n    {\n      \"description\": \"string\",\n      \"quantity\": number,\n      \"unit_price\": number, \n      \"amount\": number\n    }\n  ],\n  \"subtotal\": number,\n  \"tax_amount\": number,\n  \"total_amount\": number,\n  \"extraction_confidence\": \"high|medium|low\",\n  \"missing_fields\": [\"array of any missing required fields\"]\n}\n\nExtract ALL service categories, charges, and adjustments as separate line items. If you cannot extract certain fields, set them to null and list them in missing_fields."
        }
      },
      "id": "b3f0f2bf-e916-4084-8ac5-319dc4df361b",
      "name": "AI Invoice Data Extractor",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 1.7,
      "position": [
        -1504,
        -736
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "functionCode": "// Validate the extracted invoice data\nconst items = $input.all();\nconst results = [];\n\nfor (const item of items) {\n  try {\n    let extractedData;\n    \n    // Parse AI output if it's a string\n    if (typeof item.json.output === 'string') {\n      extractedData = JSON.parse(item.json.output);\n    } else {\n      extractedData = item.json.output || item.json;\n    }\n    \n    // Required fields for validation\n    const requiredFields = ['invoice_number', 'invoice_date', 'vendor_name', 'total_amount'];\n    const missingFields = [];\n    \n    // Check for required fields\n    for (const field of requiredFields) {\n      if (!extractedData[field] || extractedData[field] === null) {\n        missingFields.push(field);\n      }\n    }\n    \n    // Validate date format\n    const dateRegex = /^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$/;\n    if (extractedData.invoice_date && !dateRegex.test(extractedData.invoice_date)) {\n      missingFields.push('invalid_date_format');\n    }\n    \n    // Validate total amount is a number\n    if (extractedData.total_amount && isNaN(parseFloat(extractedData.total_amount))) {\n      missingFields.push('invalid_total_amount');\n    }\n    \n    // Determine validation status\n    const isValid = missingFields.length === 0;\n    const confidenceLevel = extractedData.extraction_confidence || 'unknown';\n    \n    results.push({\n      json: {\n        ...extractedData,\n        validation_status: isValid ? 'valid' : 'invalid',\n        validation_errors: missingFields,\n        confidence_level: confidenceLevel,\n        requires_manual_review: !isValid || confidenceLevel === 'low',\n        processed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n        original_file: $node['Extract PDF Text'].json.fileName\n      }\n    });\n    \n  } catch (error) {\n    results.push({\n      json: {\n        validation_status: 'error',\n        error_message: error.message,\n        validation_errors: ['parsing_error'],\n        requires_manual_review: true,\n        processed_at: new Date().toISOString(),\n        original_file: $node['Extract PDF Text'].json.fileName || 'unknown'\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\nreturn results;"
      },
